<subSubSection pageNumber="433" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="433">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="433">Note:</emphasis>
In 1767, Linnaeus simultaneously published two different epithets for this taxon: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1767" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Cometes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alterniflora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="433">C. alterniflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="433">Syst. Nat.</emphasis>
, ed. 12, 2: 127) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1767" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Cometes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="surattensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="433">C. surattensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="433">Mant. Pl.</emphasis>
: 39). The latter name has been treated as the 
<typeStatus>generitype</typeStatus>
, and is the name in current use. Rechinger (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="433">Fl. Iranica</emphasis>
144: 23. 1980) indicated Garcin material (G) as type but Linnaeus would not have seen this collection and it is not part of the original material.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
